methods.name: getPlayer
methods.description: Allows you to get statistics of player
examples: // Get player's guild along with player statshypixel.getPlayer('Minikloon', { guild: true }).then(player => {  console.log(player.guild) // null if player isn't is guild  console.log(player.guild.name) // Mini Squid  console.log(player.guild.level) // 110}).catch(e => {  console.log(e);});

// async/awaitconst player = await hypixel.getPlayer('Minikloon').catch(console.log);// If player doesn't exist, or if an error occurred ( check console )console.log(player); // null// Check if player existsif(player) console.log(player.uuid); // 20934ef9488c465180a78f861586b4cf

classes.name: Cache
classes.description: This is the default cache implementation, using a Map.All cache implementations must have these methods below, they can be async :set(key, value) : Sets key to valuehas(key) : Whether there is an entry to this key. (can be an alias to get)get(key) : Gets by key (nullish value if not found)delete(key) : Deletes by keykeys() : Array of keys, ordered by time of creation. To help you, the key will be deleted and set in case of an updatesize(): Size of cache (number of keys)clear(): Deletes all cache entriesSee JSDoc for more info

methods.name: has
methods.description: Check if there's an entry in the cache that has this keyThis doesn't have to return boolean, just a truthy/falsy value

methods.name: get
methods.description: Gets an entry, return a nullish value if not found

returns.description: Preferably, returns a boolean to check if the deletion is actually successful

methods.name: keys
methods.description: Returns Array of string (not an iterator preferably, it can break)
